-- Aston Villa Defeats West Ham 2-1 in English Premier League
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-02-10T15:30:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-10/aston-villa-defeats-west-ham-2-1-in-english-premier-league.html
Aston Villa beat West Ham 2-1 to
move out of the relegation zone in English soccer’s Premier
League today.  Christian Benteke converted a penalty and  Charles N’Zogbia 
scored from a free kick at Villa Park. West Ham’s score came
from an  Ashley Westwood  own goal late in the game.  Villa rises two places to 17th in the 20-team standings.
West Ham stays 11th. The bottom three teams are demoted at the
end of the season.  Later today league leader Manchester United hosts Everton
and can stretch its lead to 12 points after defending champion
Manchester City lost 3-1 at Southampton yesterday.  Also yesterday, Chelsea beat Wigan 4-1, Norwich and Fulham
drew 0-0, Stoke defeated Reading 2-1 and Arsenal won 1-0 at
Sunderland. Bottom club Queens Park Rangers lost 4-1 at Swansea
and Tottenham beat Newcastle 2-1. Liverpool hosts West Brom
tomorrow.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
